headline: Malaysia: TotalEnergies Signs New Renewable Power Agreement with Google to Supply Data Centers
summary: PARIS, December 16, 2025-- TotalEnergies (Paris:TTE) (LSE:TTE) (NYSE:TTE) and Google have signed a 21-year Power Purchase Agreement (PPA) to supply Google with a total volume of 1 TWh (equivalent to 20 MW) of certified renewable power from the Citra Energies solar plant in the northern Kedah province. The solar farm, which is scheduled to enter construction in early 2026, will support Google’s data center operations in Malaysia. The Malaysian Energy Commission awarded the project to TotalEnergie

headline: Where the AI trade will see 'massive bifurcation' in 2026
summary: The wait for Yahoo Finance's 2025 Company of the year is over, and the winner is private artificial intelligence giant and ChatGPT parent company OpenAI (OPAI.PVT). Yahoo Finance executive editor Brian Sozzi and Julie Hyman are joined by Sevens Report Research Founder Tom Essaye and Spear Invest founder and CIO Ivana Delevska for a conversation about how much bifurcation they anticipate in the AI trade for 2026, and their AI outlook on Big Tech players Meta Platforms (META) and Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL). Be sure to catch Brian Sozzi's full interview with OpenAI CFO Sarah Friar. Also hear this panel weigh in on OpenAI's current spending and fundraising figures and its thoughts on the existence of an AI bubble. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.
